As ROC curves and AUC measure the discrimination power between non-differentially spliced (non-DS) gene and differentially spliced (DS) gene over an interval, scientists are often interested in the discrimination power at a single cutoff point. Therefore the recall and precision at a Padj=0.05 cutoff were used as a additional set of evaluation metrics (Padj stands for multiple testing corrected p-value). Recall is equivalent to TPR while precision is the proportion of the events that test as positives that are actually true discoveries. Precision is also known as 1−falsediscoveryrate. Evaluating on precision examines whether the methods are able to control the FDR at the claimed 0.05 level. DSGseq does not return p-values and was excluded from this evaluation and SeqGSEA did not report any gene under FDR=0.05 when the sample size was 3. The results of other seven methods under the measurement of recall and precision or FDR at Padj=0.05 are summarized in Table 2.Table 2

